</node>
<node id="&quot;79TH ARMOURED DIVISION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"79th Armoured Division was the division to which the 34th Tank Brigade was assigned after its redesignation in February 1945, serving in North-west Europe from July 1944 to May 1945 under both the First Canadian Army and the British Second Army."&lt;SEP&gt;"The 79th Armoured Division is the division to which the 34th Armoured Brigade was later assigned."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0abf23caa15edfa39eb53d5e22ff1973&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22b2c8019aab1a77dd91164ed8379091</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LOUIS VUITTON CUP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Louis Vuitton Cup is the qualifying event for the America's Cup, and Emirates Team New Zealand won the right to challenge for the cup in the 34th America's Cup."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0abf23caa15edfa39eb53d5e22ff1973</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TEAM NEW ZEALAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Team New Zealand is another name for Emirates Team New Zealand, which challenged for the America's Cup in the 34th America's Cup."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0abf23caa15edfa39eb53d5e22ff1973</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AMERICA'S CUP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"America's Cup is the oldest trophy in international sport, and the 34th America's Cup was a significant event in its history."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0abf23caa15edfa39eb53d5e22ff1973</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHURCHILL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Churchill is mentioned as the type of tank equipment used by the 34th Armoured Brigade."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0abf23caa15edfa39eb53d5e22ff1973</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;34TH ARMY TANK BRIGADE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"34th Army Tank Brigade was formed in 1941 and later redesignated as the 34th Tank Brigade in February 1945, serving in the 79th Armoured Division and providing close support for infantry assaults. It was equipped with Churchill tanks and served in North-west Europe from July 1944 to May 1945, under both the First Canadian Army and the British Second Army before being disbanded in early 1946."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22b2c8019aab1a77dd91164ed8379091</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;34TH TANK BRIGADE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"34th Tank Brigade was formed in 1941 and later redesignated as the 34th Tank Brigade in February 1945, serving in the 79th Armoured Division and providing close support for infantry assaults. It was equipped with Churchill tanks and served in North-west Europe from July 1944 to May 1945, under both the First Canadian Army and the British Second Army before being disbanded in early 1946."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22b2c8019aab1a77dd91164ed8379091</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHURCHILL TANKS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Churchill tanks were the primary equipment of the 34th Tank Brigade, used for providing close support to infantry assaults during World War II."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22b2c8019aab1a77dd91164ed8379091</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NORTH-WEST EUROPE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"North-west Europe is the region where the 34th Tank Brigade served from July 1944 to May 1945, under both the First Canadian Army and the British Second Army."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22b2c8019aab1a77dd91164ed8379091</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FIRST CANADIAN ARMY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"First Canadian Army was one of the armies under which the 34th Tank Brigade served in North-west Europe from July 1944 to May 1945."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22b2c8019aab1a77dd91164ed8379091</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BRITISH SECOND ARMY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"British Second Army was one of the armies under which the 34th Tank Brigade served in North-west Europe from July 1944 to May 1945."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22b2c8019aab1a77dd91164ed8379091</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANDRÉS AVELINO CÁCERES DORREGARAY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Andrés Avelino Cáceres Dorregaray served as the President of Peru three times during the 19th century, from 1881 to 1882 as the 34th President of Peru, then from 1886 to 1890 as the 36th President of Peru, and again from 1894 to 1895 as the 38th President of Peru. He is considered a national hero for leading the resistance to Chilean occupation during the War of the Pacific (1879–1883), where he fought as a General in the Peruvian Army."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22b2c8019aab1a77dd91164ed8379091</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PERU&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Peru is the country where Andrés Avelino Cáceres Dorregaray served as President and led the resistance against Chilean occupation during the War of the Pacific."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22b2c8019aab1a77dd91164ed8379091</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WAR OF THE PACIFIC&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"War of the Pacific (1879–1883) was a conflict where Andrés Avelino Cáceres Dorregaray led the Peruvian resistance against Chilean occupation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22b2c8019aab1a77dd91164ed8379091</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHILEAN OCCUPATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Chilean occupation refers to the period during the War of the Pacific when Chilean forces occupied parts of Peru."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22b2c8019aab1a77dd91164ed8379091</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;R ADAMS COWLEY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"R Adams Cowley (July 25, 1917 – October 27, 1991) was an American surgeon known as the 'Father of Trauma Medicine' and a pioneer in trauma medicine."&lt;SEP&gt;"R Adams Cowley was an American surgeon and pioneer in emergency medicine, known for founding the United States's first trauma center and creating the 'Golden Hour' concept."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b2821d62cd4c5aad9fe951ada9103c47&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22b2c8019aab1a77dd91164ed8379091</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 24}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 116}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TRAUMA MEDICINE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Trauma medicine is the field pioneered by R Adams Cowley, focusing on the treatment and management of traumatic injuries."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22b2c8019aab1a77dd91164ed8379091</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 24}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 116}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UNITED STATES ARMY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The United States Army provided funding for Dr. Cowley's research on shock in people, marking the first such award in the U.S."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b2821d62cd4c5aad9fe951ada9103c47</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 24}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 116}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UNIVERSITY OF MARYLAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The University of Maryland is mentioned as a previous coaching position for Paul W. Bryant before he joined the University of Alabama."&lt;SEP&gt;"The University of Maryland is where Dr. Cowley founded the United States's first trauma center in 1958."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-66009cc5c47a2f028b2acf9fe3b8f0fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2821d62cd4c5aad9fe951ada9103c47</data>
