  <data key="d1">"Eric Cartman is a character from the animated TV series 'South Park', known for his muffled and indiscernible speech due to his parka hood covering his mouth, and was first introduced on television in 1997."&lt;SEP&gt;"Eric Cartman is a main character in 'South Park', known for his selfish and often cruel behavior, who appears in both 'Tonsil Trouble' and 'Cartman Gets an Anal Probe'."&lt;SEP&gt;"Eric Cartman is a main character in 'South Park', known for his selfish and often cruel behavior, who is introduced in the episode 'Cartman Gets an Anal Probe' and later infects Kyle with HIV in 'Tonsil Trouble'."&lt;SEP&gt;"Eric Cartman is a main character in the animated series South Park, one of the four primary characters, alongside Kenny McCormick, Stan Marsh, and Kyle Broflovski."&lt;SEP&gt;"Eric Cartman is one of the central characters in 'South Park', alongside Kyle Broflovski, Stan Marsh, and Kenny McCormick."&lt;SEP&gt;"Eric Cartman is one of the central characters in the animated television series 'South Park', alongside Stan Marsh, Kyle Broflovski, and Kenny McCormick."&lt;SEP&gt;"Eric Cartman, often referred to as just Cartman, is a main character in the animated television series South Park, created by Matt Stone and Trey Parker, and voiced by Trey Parker."</data>
