<node id="&quot;LEUCOSTOMA CANKER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DISEASE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Leucostoma canker is a fungal disease affecting stone fruits ('Prunus' spp.), caused by several plant pathogens including 'Leucostoma persoonii', 'Leucostoma cinctum', 'Cytospora leucostoma', and 'Cytospora cincta'. The disease can manifest in various symptoms depending on the part of the tree infected, with the most lethal symptom being Leucostoma cankers. Management strategies include cultural practices and chemical treatments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-02fe458aec765b933ac78eb21776e03b</data>
