<node id="&quot;MAREK'S DISEASE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DISEASE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Marek's disease is a highly contagious viral neoplastic disease in chickens, named after József Marek, a Hungarian veterinarian, and caused by an alphaherpesvirus known as 'Marek's disease virus' (MDV) or 'Gallid herpesvirus 2' (GaHV-2)."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marek's disease is a viral disease in poultry caused by the Marek's disease virus, which can be prevented using certain vaccine strains."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8d825c4ead81ee80f3f1def08830c65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d7a3e02dea60efd2006af1fc5b31d7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;JÓZSEF MAREK&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"József Marek is a Hungarian veterinarian after whom Marek's disease is named."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8d825c4ead81ee80f3f1def08830c65</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHICKENS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SPECIES"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Chickens are the hosts of Marek's disease, a highly contagious viral neoplastic disease."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8d825c4ead81ee80f3f1def08830c65</data>
</node>
