  <data key="d2">chunk-d8d825c4ead81ee80f3f1def08830c65</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ALPHAHERPESVIRUS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Alphaherpesvirus is a type of virus that causes Marek's disease in chickens."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8d825c4ead81ee80f3f1def08830c65</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GALLID HERPESVIRUS 2&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Gallid herpesvirus 2 (GaHV-2) is the specific strain of alphaherpesvirus that causes Marek's disease in chickens."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8d825c4ead81ee80f3f1def08830c65</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;T CELL LYMPHOMA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"T cell lymphoma is a characteristic feature of Marek's disease, involving the infiltration of T cells into nerves and organs."&lt;SEP&gt;"T cell lymphoma is a type of cancer that can be caused by the GaHV-2 virus."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8d825c4ead81ee80f3f1def08830c65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d7a3e02dea60efd2006af1fc5b31d7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LYMPHOCYTES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CELL TYPE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Lymphocytes are immune cells that infiltrate nerves and organs in Marek's disease."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8d825c4ead81ee80f3f1def08830c65</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GAHV-2&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"GaHV-2 is a virus known for causing T cell lymphoma and infiltrating nerves and organs with lymphocytes, and it can persist in birds for life."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6d7a3e02dea60efd2006af1fc5b31d7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MDV&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"MDV stands for Marek's disease virus, which appears to have related viruses that can be used as vaccine strains."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6d7a3e02dea60efd2006af1fc5b31d7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HERPESVIRUS OF TURKEYS (HVT)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"HVT is a related virus to MDV that causes no apparent disease in turkeys and is used as a vaccine strain for preventing Marek's disease."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6d7a3e02dea60efd2006af1fc5b31d7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DANDER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dander is a substance that can carry and transmit the virus."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6d7a3e02dea60efd2006af1fc5b31d7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEATHER FOLLICLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Feather follicles are the source of dander from which the virus spreads."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6d7a3e02dea60efd2006af1fc5b31d7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MATERNAL ANTIBODIES&quot;">
