  <data key="d0">"ORGANISM"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Horses are one of the species most commonly affected by the West Nile virus."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-127ebc0fa04611a47e70bf0d115ab30a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 17}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HUMANS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANISM"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Humans can contract the West Nile virus from infected mosquitoes, although the first human cases typically appear several months after infected birds are present."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-127ebc0fa04611a47e70bf0d115ab30a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 17}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CARDIAC FIBROSIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cardiac fibrosis is a medical condition characterized by the abnormal thickening of heart valves due to the inappropriate proliferation of cardiac fibroblasts or the excess deposition of extracellular matrix in cardiac muscle, leading to stiffer and less compliant muscle tissue and often progressing to heart failure."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6d8cd6ccdcadea2753d7b8be85af95b9</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HEART MUSCLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Heart muscle is another term for cardiac muscle, which is responsible for pumping blood and maintaining circulation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Heart muscle, also known as cardiac muscle, is an involuntary, striated muscle found in the walls and histological foundation of the heart, specifically the myocardium. It is one of three major types of muscle, alongside skeletal and smooth muscle, and forms through the process of myogenesis."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8ba3bf306b23bd9000825114cbf1e09d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d8cd6ccdcadea2753d7b8be85af95b9</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANIMATED SHORT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An animated short is a brief animated film, such as 'Jesus vs. Frosty' and 'Jesus vs. Santa', where Cartman first appeared in a prototypical form in 1992 and 1995."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6d8cd6ccdcadea2753d7b8be85af95b9</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PILOT EPISODE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A pilot episode is the first episode of a television series, such as 'Cartman Gets an Anal Probe', where Cartman first appeared on television in 1997."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6d8cd6ccdcadea2753d7b8be85af95b9</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;1997&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"1997 is the year in which the pilot episode 'Cartman Gets an Anal Probe' aired, marking Cartman's first appearance on television."&lt;SEP&gt;"1997 is the year the Octopus card system was introduced to replace the common stored value ticket system in Hong Kong."&lt;SEP&gt;"1997 is the year the athlete won the gold medal at the 1997 Pan American Junior Athletics Championships."&lt;SEP&gt;"1997 is the year the contactless smart card system was launched."&lt;SEP&gt;"1997 marks the year when the Washington State Cougars football team represented Washington State University in the Pacific-10 Conference during the 1997 NCAA Division I-A football season."&lt;SEP&gt;"1997 was the year of the Pan American Junior Athletics Championships where Shane Niemi won the gold medal in the 400 metres."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-da86b66442cd64f499718579872b28ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d8cd6ccdcadea2753d7b8be85af95b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba1ca1046626f5874be19c14e31f0840&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-334a8ff489e95639c55cd343f2116538&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a55825fd634da16f455319a134011ee2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f17a12582e5fef088b11b266ad26fc60</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 55}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 163}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CARDIAC MUSCLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cardiac muscle is a specialized type of muscle tissue that makes up the heart, responsible for pumping blood throughout the body."&lt;SEP&gt;"Cardiac muscle is one of the three major types of muscle, forming in the process of myogenesis and consisting of cardiomyocytes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Cardiac muscle is part of the heart and is affected by myocardial infarction (MI)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-649f59d1c11cc7f8539ec5867caf4797&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bec8133eda961d41175415245108990e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ba3bf306b23bd9000825114cbf1e09d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 26}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 124}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 190}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SKELETAL MUSCLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Skeletal muscle is one of the three major types of muscle, forming in the process of myogenesis and consisting of multinucleated muscle fibers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bec8133eda961d41175415245108990e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SMOOTH MUSCLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Smooth muscle is one of the three major types of muscle, forming in the process of myogenesis and not specifically mentioned in the text."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bec8133eda961d41175415245108990e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MYOCARDIUM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Myocardium is the muscle tissue of the heart, forming a thick middle layer between the outer epicardium layer and the inner endocardium layer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bec8133eda961d41175415245108990e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 26}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 124}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 191}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CARDIOMYOCYTES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cardiomyocytes are specialized cells that make up the cardiac muscle, containing myofibrils and showing striations similar to skeletal muscle cells. They have a high mitochondrial density, allowing them to produce ATP quickly and resist fatigue."&lt;SEP&gt;"Cardiomyocytes are the muscle cells that make up the cardiac muscle, containing one to four nuclei and forming intercalated discs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bec8133eda961d41175415245108990e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ba3bf306b23bd9000825114cbf1e09d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 26}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 124}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 190}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTERCALATED DISC&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Intercalated discs are microscopic identifying features of cardiac muscle, supporting synchronized contraction and occurring at the Z line of the sarcomere."</data>
