<node id="&quot;MYOCARDIAL INFARCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Myocardial infarction, commonly known as a heart attack, is an event where blood flow to a part of the heart decreases or stops, causing damage to the heart muscle. It is characterized by chest pain, shortness of breath, nausea, and other symptoms."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8ba3bf306b23bd9000825114cbf1e09d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 26}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SKELETAL MUSCLE CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Skeletal muscle cells are cells that form the skeletal muscles, which are multinucleated and have striations similar to cardiomyocytes but differ in their number of nuclei and function."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8ba3bf306b23bd9000825114cbf1e09d</data>
